text:
Walk pass and decided to buy the red bean bun for a try.
The bread is soft and came with a pack of 4 small bun.
Opening it and tasted the red bean is smooth and soft (not too dry or wet).  If they could put a litter more of the red bean will be fantastic and super!
Overall, could try their others products.

This neighborhood old-school bakery has been around since my school days (2000s), but it’s no longer like before.

Bought a birthday cake from them on 21 May 2022 to celebrate my mom’s birthday. Paid $30 and was told it’s a discount from $33. Cake is large (30cm) but felt very light in the box. At that moment I felt I overpaid for it but let it go cos the design is cute.

Upon cutting the cake it has a crumbly texture and did not look smooth. It is dry and the taste is disappointing.

While eating, we found 2 large pieces of eggshell buried within it, it was horrendous.

We ate the leftover cake today and found a third piece of eggshell. Just look at its size.

This will be the last time I buy from this bakery.
been buying from this shop for years!! love the bread and especially the waffles

My recent visit to the bakery store was marred by an unfortunate encounter with the staff member in charge of baking waffles. Despite my anticipation for a pleasant experience, I was met with rudeness and indifference. The lady responsible for baking waffles displayed unprofessional behavior. I hope management addresses this issue promptly to maintain the bakery's reputation for quality service.
I have always visited this cake shop since I was young. Bread is fresh and affordable so are the waffles, lots of traditional snacks too
